In this version of the application we have added a machine learning model that can detect toxic and offensive messages. Now we can analyze messages directly on your mobile device before sending them to the chat. This ensures privacy and data protection as messages are transmitted in an encrypted format. With this enhancement users can enjoy a safe and friendly interaction within our application. If the model detects that the entered text is toxic or offensive the user will see a corresponding emoji below the input field.

You asked and we listened! The possibility to share a QR code is added. Here s the step by step instruction. Create a chat the button in the upper right corner and think up a password a QR code will appear. Tap it with your finger and choose a sharing method. To be on the safe side we made a hint in the upper right corner. The person on the other end clicks the QR code icon in the upper left corner of the app scans the QR code or selects received one from you from the photo gallery enters your password the chat is created! It s a good practice to delete the password and QR code from the messages and the photo gallery after that. Also we added a hint about the swipe actions a vertical bar to the right of the chat name.
